    the 1780s and who was also involved in a good deal of philanthropic work.  The contacts are 
    all associated with dissent and there is nothing to suggest that either John or Edward Topham 
    had dissenting links; indeed, the former becomes Librarian to the Archbishop of Canterbury in 1790. </p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> There is evidence that Edward Topham may have moved in Godwin's circles. Holcroft refers 
